Across the country, health care and domestic workers lack key health and workplace protections as COVID-19 continues to spread.
If nurses and health care workers are not protected from COVID-19, experts and advocates say, then the public is not protected.
Thomason said paid sick leave for all health care workers is absolutely vital for containing the pandemic.
One such place is southern Louisiana, where many nurses and health care workers are not unionized and labor protections are notoriously lax.
Until more information comes to light, hospitals should adhere to the “precautionary principle,” which states that health care providers should not wait until scientists know for sure how the virus spreads to implement measures protecting health care workers.